    "Reason : 1 - This proposal CONSTITUTES DEVELOPMENT within the meaning of Section 55 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and a planning application IS REQUIRED. \r\n\r\nIn the absence of side elevations and details of materials, Officers have not been able to  ascertain whether the proposed rear dormer roof extension would comply with criteria B.1(d) and conditions B.2(a)(b)(c) of Class B Part 1 Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).\r\n",
